<p>Frog, &quot;noir&quot; is a genre of detective stories, a descendant of &quot;film noir&quot;, a filmic style often seen in the classic detective flicks of the '40s and '50s (sometimes starring Humphrey Bogart). Noir tales feature a hard-boiled detective, corrupt officials, large criminal organizations, and police interrogation techniques that might be regarded as a bit crude and violent by the KGB.</p>
